{
  "experiment": "D3_NSCLC_v1 -- Can IRDME structural position (delta-r) predict cancer drug sensitivity (PRISM)?",
  "description": "First direct test of IRDME as a drug discovery tool. The Oncogenic Decoupling Signature (ODS) predicts structural dampers are cancer-essential. This experiment tests whether that structural position also predicts drug sensitivity: drugs targeting structural dampers should show stronger cancer cell killing than drugs targeting structural anchors. If confirmed, IRDME can rank drug targets from network structure alone, without any wet-lab screening.",
